# Open-Enroll UI Consistency

> **Consistency over creativity.** Always follow existing patterns unless explicitly asked to innovate.
> When in doubt, copy a reference component (see bottom of file) rather than inventing a new approach.

## Allowed tools (use these for all new/modified UI)

- **Tailwind CSS** for all styling — no custom CSS files, no inline `style={{}}`, no CSS-in-JS, no `sx` props.
- **Lucide React** for all icons (`import { Icon } from 'lucide-react'`) — no other icon libraries.
- **Native HTML elements** (`div`, `button`, `table`, `input`, …) styled with Tailwind classes.

## Material-UI: no new usage, keep existing

MUI (`@mui/*`, including `x-data-grid` and `x-date-pickers`) is **legacy** — present in ~38 files
(mostly `components/commissions`, `pages/tenant-admin`, `pages/groups`, `components/ai`).

- **Do not add MUI to new or modified code** — build with Tailwind + Lucide + native HTML.
- **Leave existing MUI screens working.** Convert a file to Tailwind only when you're already
  editing it for another reason — never do a drive-by rewrite of a working MUI screen.
- Ant Design, Chakra, and other component/icon libraries are not used — don't introduce them.

## Brand colors — use the `oe-*` tokens, NOT raw Tailwind blues

Brand colors are CSS variables defined in `frontend/tailwind.config.js` and re-themed per tenant at runtime by `BrandingContext`. Hardcoding `blue-600` breaks tenant theming.

| Purpose                     | Use this                                                              | Never use                          |
| --------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Primary / interactive       | `bg-oe-primary hover:bg-oe-dark text-white` (sky `#1f8dbf` / `#125e82`) | `bg-blue-600`, `hover:bg-blue-700` |
| Light accent / backgrounds  | `bg-oe-light` (`#d6eef8`)                                              | `bg-blue-50`, `bg-blue-100`        |
| Focus ring                  | `focus:ring-2 focus:ring-oe-primary`                                  | `focus:ring-blue-500`              |
| Text links / primary text   | `text-oe-primary` / `text-oe-dark`                                    | `text-blue-600`                    |
| Success                     | `text-oe-success` (`#4caf50`)                                         | —                                  |
| Error / danger              | `text-red-600 hover:bg-red-50` (or `text-oe-error`)                   | —                                  |
| Secondary / outline button  | `border border-gray-300 text-gray-700 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50`     | —                                  |

> **Never use raw Tailwind blues (`blue-600`, `blue-700`, `blue-50`, `ring-blue-500`) for buttons, links, focus rings, or any interactive element.** Gray scale (`gray-50`…`gray-900`) and semantic status colors (`red-*`, `yellow-*`, `green-*`) for badges/alerts are fine.

## Layout & spacing

- Containers: `div` with Tailwind classes.
- Standard page padding: `p-6`.
- Card: `bg-white rounded-lg border border-gray-200`.
- Card section header: `p-6 border-b border-gray-200`; content area: `p-6`.

## Typography

- Page title: `<h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">`
- Section title: `<h2 class="text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">`
- Description: `<p class="text-gray-600">`

## Interactive elements

- Buttons: `px-4 py-2 rounded-lg` + the color tokens above.
- Inputs / selects: `px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg focus:ring-2 focus:ring-oe-primary`.
- Disabled: `disabled:bg-gray-50 disabled:opacity-50`.

## Forms

- Labels: `<label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">`
- Input groups: `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4`
- Validation: red border for errors (`border-red-300`); always pair inputs with labels for accessibility.

## Data display

- Stats cards: responsive grid, e.g. `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-4`.
- Tables: native `table` with `min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200`.
- Badges: `inline-flex px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold rounded-full` + status color (`bg-green-100 text-green-800`, `bg-red-100 text-red-800`, `bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800`).
- Loading skeletons: `animate-pulse` with gray backgrounds.

## Status banners / feedback

- Success: `bg-green-50 border border-green-200 text-green-800`
- Error: `bg-red-50 border border-red-200 text-red-800`
- Warning: `bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 text-yellow-800`
- Info: `bg-oe-light border border-oe-primary/30 text-oe-dark`

## Icons (Lucide React only)

- Sizes: `h-4 w-4` (small), `h-5 w-5` (medium), `h-6 w-6` (large).
- Spacing from text: `mr-2` / `ml-2`.

## Responsive

- Mobile-first; layer with `sm:` `md:` `lg:` `xl:` prefixes.

## Forbidden (in new / modified code)

❌ New Material-UI usage · new Ant / Chakra components, icons, or hooks · `sx` props
❌ Custom CSS files · inline `style={{}}` · CSS-in-JS
❌ Raw Tailwind blues for interactive elements (`blue-600`, `blue-700`, `ring-blue-500`, …)
❌ Custom animations beyond Tailwind utilities without explicit permission

